flash.tools.debugger.events

Class FaultEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • flash.tools.debugger.events.DebugEvent
      • flash.tools.debugger.events.FaultEvent
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConsoleErrorFault, DivideByZeroFault, ExceptionFault, InvalidTargetFault, InvalidURLFault, InvalidWithFault, ProtoLimitFault, RecursionLimitFault, ScriptTimeoutFault, StackUnderFlowFault

    public abstract class FaultEvent
extends DebugEvent
    An event type that signals a problem situation within the Player. Under normal conditions the Player will suspend execution, resulting in a following BreakEvent to be fired. However, if this occurs while a getter or setter is executing, then the player will *not* suspend execution.

      • stackTrace

        public String stackTrace()
        Returns the callstack in exactly the format that it came back from the player. That is, as a single string of the following form: 
                        at functionName()[filename:lineNumber]
                at functionName()[filename:lineNumber]
                ...
        Each line has a leading tab character.
        Returns:
        callstack, or an empty string; never null
